&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datavant is seeking a detail-oriented and customer-focused &lt;strong&gt;Release of Information (ROI) Health Information Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to support a medical facility in&amp;nbsp;Kalamazoo, MI. &amp;nbsp;This role is responsible for processing medical record requests, maintaining HIPAA compliance, and ensuring accurate and timely release of protected health information (PHI).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is organized, adaptable, and experienced in electronic medical record (EMR) systems. This position requires the ability to multitask in a fast-paced healthcare environment while maintaining strict confidentiality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💼&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Release of Information (ROI) requests accurately and efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retrieve and compile medical records from EMR systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure HIPAA compliance when handling all protected health information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and generate reports as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform administrative functions related to ROI processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized documentation and tracking of requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with healthcare staff, patients, and requestors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide coverage support when onsite staff are out (PTO/call-outs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain productivity and quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎓&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Training &amp;amp; Onboarding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
